               <listApp>
                   <app/>
               </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>To the Great Hero and τhe gods who share the temple, the landowners of the city, the ninth year, Pachon 25.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>A dedication to an unnamed ‘Great Hero’ and other temple-sharing gods (synnaoi theoi), by the landowners ‘from the polis’ (presumably Alexandrians who have land in the Sebennyte Nome). There is some uncertainty about the provenance of the inscription. Rubensohn 1913 reported it as ’Mehallet el-Kebir’ in the Delta, an unattested toponym, but A. Bernand suggested El-Mahalla el-Kubra (see I. Varsovie, p. 153, Trismegistos GEO 3669).</p> 
            </div>
